newsitem.title: AUSTRALIA: RTRS-Oil Search says Moran-1X oil-bearing.
newsitem.headline: RTRS-Oil Search says Moran-1X oil-bearing.

text.p: Oil Search Ltd said on Friday that data collected from the Moran-1X well in the central Papuan highlands showed it was oil-bearing.
"RFT data has been obtained over the sandstone interval 2,926 metres to 2,975 metres in the Moran-1X well, and this data indicates that the interval is oil bearing," Oil Search said.
On Wednesday Oil Search said its initial tests had had shown the interval was hydrocarbon bearing.

Moran-1X, in permit PDL-2, is located 11 km north of the Agogo processing facilities which form the northernmost extension of the Kutubu facilities and is five km west of the 1996 Paua-1X oil discovery.
The main objective of the Moran-1X well are to evaluate the Toro, Digimu and Iagifu Sandstones, Oil Search said.
On Wednesday Oil Search said its initial tests had shown the interval was hydrocarbon bearing.
No sample was recovered from the interval because of the failure of a tool.
"Electric logs run over the bottom section of the well indicate that the other sandstone reservoirs in the well were water-bearing," Oil Search said.
The current programme is for 7-inch casing to be set and the well drilled to an anticipated total depth of 3,960 metres, Oil Search said.
Subsequent to the well reaching total depth, a number of drill stem tests are planned for the interval 2,926 to 2,975 metres.

PDL-2 licence holders participating in the well are Oil Search 7.763 percent, the PNG-state owned Petroleum Resources Kutubu Pty Ltd 22.50 percent, JPP 4.844 percent and units of Chevron Corp (operator) 19.375 percent, Mobil Corp's Ampolex Ltd, 16.455 percent, The British
Petroleum Co Plc 19.375 percent and The Broken Hill Pty Co Ltd 9.688 percent.
